## Decisions / Interpretation
- Kept the file at scripts/ (NOT moved to .github/). Rationale: last turn the user
  asked to put it \"in python alongside the workflow\" and accepted scripts/
  (which matches the repo convention scripts/slack_digest.py +
  slack-digest.yml). \"Alongside the workflow\" in their vocabulary has meant \"a
  real file the workflow invokes,\" so this message reads as \"the bash is still
  inline -- move it into the file too,\" which is what was done. If they actually
  want the file physically under .github/, it's a trivial git mv follow-up.
- Chose env (DRY_RUN) over a GitHub expression ternary
  (${{ inputs.dry_run && '--dry-run' || '' }}) so ALL logic lives in the file and
  the run: line is a pure invocation, not even an Actions expression.

